        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 27 at 3:24PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 324 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles south of Trujillo, or 32 miles north of Santa Rosa, moving
northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Trujillo and Trementina.

This includes State Road 104 between Mile Markers 30 and 49.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
